Heat broiler to high. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @potatoes{16%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. Strip @thyme{¼%ounce} leaves from stems; roughly chop. Trim, peel, and halve @carrot{3%ounce} lengthwise; slice crosswise into ¼-inch-thick half-moons. Finely dice @celery{2.5%ounce}. Halve, peel, and finely chop @onion{1}. Peel and mince @garlic{1%clove}.

Place potatoes in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Drain and return potatoes to #pot{}. Mash with @sour cream{3%tablespoon}, @butter{1%tablespoon}, and 1 tsp chopped thyme until smooth and creamy, adding splashes of water as needed. Season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Cover to keep warm.

== Filling ==

While potatoes cook, heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tablespoon} in a #medium ovenproof pan{} over medium-high heat. Add carrot; season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring, until slightly softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add celery, onion, and a large drizzle of oil; season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring, until veggies are just tender, ~{5-7%minutes}.

> If veggies begin to brown too quickly, add a splash of water.

Stir in garlic and 2 tsp chopped thyme; cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Remove sausage from casing if necessary; discard casing. Add @chopped chicken breast{10%ounce} to pan with veggies. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Add @tomato paste{1} and @flour{1%tablespoon}; cook, stirring, until thoroughly combined, ~{1%minute}.

> TIP: If swapping in chicken or chicken sausage, no need to break up into pieces!

Gradually stir @water{½%cup} into pan with sausage mixture.

Stir in @beef stock concentrate{1} and bring to a boil. Cook until mixture is very thick, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Taste and season with salt and pepper.

> If your pan isn't ovenproof, transfer filling now to a baking dish.

== Assembly ==

Top filling with an even layer of mashed potatoes, leaving a 1-inch border around edge of pan. Evenly sprinkle mashed potatoes with @white cheddar cheese{½%cup}. Broil until browned, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> Watch carefully to avoid burning.

Let rest at least ~{5%minutes}, then divide between plates and serve.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.